# Hands-On Penetration Testing Experience

As part of my cybersecurity training and self-study journey, I have completed a variety of practical labs and challenge environments across Hack The Box, TryHackMe, and investigative Sherlock scenarios. These labs provided hands-on experience in penetration testing methodologies, reconnaissance, enumeration, vulnerability assessment, privilege escalation, web application security, and post-exploitation techniques.

Throughout these exercises, I worked with both Linux and Windows environments, applying real-world penetration testing approaches and developing a structured methodology for identifying and analyzing security weaknesses.

## Featured Labs

### FriendZone

Performed reconnaissance, service enumeration, web application analysis, and privilege escalation techniques in a controlled environment.

### TeamWork (Sherlock)

Conducted investigative analysis, evidence collection, and incident response-style research to identify attacker activity and reconstruct events.

### Lame

Practiced vulnerability identification, exploitation validation, and system enumeration techniques within a vulnerable Linux environment.

### Beep

Explored common security weaknesses in network services and web applications while applying enumeration and exploitation methodologies.

### Nineveh

Performed in-depth web application testing, service analysis, and privilege escalation techniques to gain a deeper understanding of attack chains.

### Active

Worked with Active Directory concepts, domain enumeration, and privilege analysis in a Windows enterprise environment.

### Access

Focused on Windows security assessments, credential discovery, and post-exploitation concepts.

### SalineBreeze (Sherlock)

Applied threat investigation techniques, log analysis, and attacker methodology research in a forensic-style scenario.

### Attacking GoldenEye

Conducted web application and infrastructure assessments while identifying security weaknesses and attack vectors.

### Attacking Blogger

Performed web application security testing, reconnaissance, and vulnerability validation techniques.

### Attacking DC4

Practiced penetration testing methodology from initial enumeration through privilege escalation and system compromise analysis.

